SUMMARIZER="B">    

A U.S. military F-16C crashed today in a remote area of Iwate
Prefecture (State) about 290 miles north of Tokyo.  The pilot,
Maj. Wyman E. Vanedoe, baled out safely and was taken by a Japanese
rescue helicopter to Misawa Air Base where he is listed in good
condition.  The aircraft from the 14th Tactical Fighter Squadron at
Misawa was on a routine training flight when it crashed.  About 50
F-16s are stationed at Misawa.  On March 22, 1987, another F-16
crashed in the Pacific Ocean off Misawa, 360 miles north of Tokyo.  In
that crash the pilot was also rescued.</SUM>

<SUM
